Introduction
This document constitutes the information envisaged by Art. 13 of EU Regulation No 679/2016 (“GDPR”) relating to the collection and processing of personal data in the context of the use of the services offered by the Company
Oryx Technology
(hereinafter the “Company”), allowing the use of the application “Buraco Plus”, and describes the ways in which we collect, store, use and manage information (including personal information) provided directly or indirectly when the user connects with our websites or mobile applications in order to use the gaming service referred to “Buraco Plus” (hereinafter also “Services”).

The responsibility of Oryx Technology in the processing of users’ personal data, and referred to in this Privacy Policy, is strictly limited to information collected or received directly from the website and / or the “Buraco Plus” application, and is expressly excluded with reference to the processing of data and information carried out by websites or applications owned by third parties, even in the presence of a link.

By accessing and / or using our Services, the user consents to the processing and dissemination of personal data as required by this policy.
1. Holder of the treatment
The holder of the treatment of personal data is the company’s Oryx Technology, based in Doha (Qatar), P.O. Box 24186, email:
support@oryxtechs.com
.
2. Place and methods of treatment
The data is processed using data processing tools with servers available to the Company, located in Italy, and is carried out by technical employees, the expressly instructed by the Owner. No data deriving from the use of services is disclosed to third parties without the consent of the person concerned, with the exception of cases where this is strictly functional to make a customer service required (eg. for the purposes of payment of the membership fees), or to perform services on our behalf (eg. data analysis and customer service provision).
3. Type of data collected, corresponding purpose and legal basis
The data processor collects the following types of data:
A)
Navigation data:
The computer systems and software procedures for the provision of services acquire certain personal data transmitted by the use of Internet communication protocols. This information is not collected to be associated with identified, but by their very nature could, through processing and associations with data held by third parties, to identify users.
These data are:
the website from which you called our page ( “referral” cd);
the IP address and the domain names of the devices used by users to use the Services, and the “device id (name and model of the device used);
the date and time of the request or access;
the same request from the browser or other client in the form of URI (Uniform Resource Identifier);
technical code of http response obtained from the server (error, successful, etc.);
the amount of data transmitted;
the browser, its technical and functional features and operating system used.
These data will be used by the owner for the sole purpose of obtaining anonymous statistical information on use of the Services, to identify your favorite pages by users and, therefore, in order to provide more adequate content and control its correct functioning. At the request of the competent authorities, in accordance with art. 25, paragraph 2 of Legislative Decree no. 196/03, the data may be communicated to them for purposes of defense or state security or the prevention, detection or suppression of crime. The data of the type described above are necessary for the provision of services. Their absence makes it impossible to benefit from the same services.
