7. Rights of
In accordance with Articles 15-22 of the GDPR the user has the following rights:
right of access
: the user has the right to obtain from the data controller confirmation as to whether or not the current processing of personal data concerning him and, if so, to gain access to personal data;
right of reply
: the user has the right to obtain from the data controller the rectification of inaccurate personal data relating to him without undue delay.Given the purpose of the treatment, the person has the right to obtain the integration of incomplete personal data, even providing a supplementary statement;
right to be forgotten
: the user has the right to obtain from the data controller the erasure of personal data concerning him;
right to limitation of the treatment
: the user has the right to obtain from the data controller the limitation of treatment when engaging one of the cases provided for by art. 18 of the GDPR, or in the event of inaccuracy, unlawfulness, opposition for legitimate reasons on the part of the interested party or are necessary for the interested party to ascertain, exercise or defend a right in court;
right to portability
: the user has the right to receive in a structured format, common and readable by automatic device using the personal data concerning him or supplied to a controller and have the right to transmit such data to another data controller treatment unimpeded by the data controller which provided them.
The user also has the right to object at any time, for reasons relating to his particular situation, to the processing of personal data concerning him or her, unless the data controller does not demonstrate the existence of legitimate reasons to proceed to treatment prevail over interests, on the rights and freedoms of. To this end, it may ask the same Oryx Technology by sending an email to
support@oryxtechs.com
, or by writing to the Company’s headquarters.

The user has the further right to complain to the relevant supervisory authority considers that are violated the rights they enjoy under the present conditions and rules established within the GDPR.

Finally, please note that the consent to the processing of its data can be revoked at any time by sending a communication to the addresses indicated above.
8. Cookies
The Company Oryx Technology uses cookies and other similar technologies (HTML5 Local Storage) within the application “Buraco Plus”. Cookies are short strings of text (letters and / or numbers) that allow the web server to store on the client (browser or device) information to be reused during the same visit to the service (cd. Session cookies) or later, even after several days (cd. persistent cookies). Cookies are stored, according to user preferences from a single browser on the specific device used (PC, tablet, smartphone). In the remainder of this document the term “cookies” will be indicated, in addition to cookies, also similar technologies.

 

We and our marketing and outsourcing partners, affiliates, or analytics service providers use technologies such as cookies, beacons, scripts, and tags to identify a user’s computer/device and to “remember” things about your visit, such as your preferences or a user name and password.  Information contained in a cookie may be linked to your personal information, such as your user ID, for purposes such as improving the quality of our Services, tailoring recommendations to your interests, and making the Service easier to use.  You can disable cookies at any time, although you may not be able to access or use features of the Service.

 

We use mobile analytics software to allow us to better understand the functionality of our Mobile Software on your device. This software may record information such as how often you use the application, the events that occur within the application, aggregated usage, performance data, and where the application was downloaded from. We do not link the information we store within the analytics software to any personal information you submit within the mobile application.
8.1 Types of cookies, aims and its management
The application “Buraco Plus” use the following types of cookies:
Cookies technicians:
these cookies are strictly necessary for the provision and use of services, allowing navigation of the pages, the sharing of any content, storing the credentials of access to services and to maintain the preferences manifested active. The deactivation of these cookies impairs the use of the site and the services offered through it. If you wish not to receive this type of cookies you are invited not to access the Services.
Cookies analysis and performance:
these cookies allow the data processor to know the ways of use of the Services by the users in general, in order to monitor and improve its content and method of delivery of the same. All information collected by these cookies is anonymous and not linked to personal information. The collection of this information may be made through third-party services that anonymize making the data not traceable to individuals (so-called “single-in”). If you wish not to receive this type of cookies you are invited not to access the Services.
Cookies profiling:
these cookies are used to identify the individual user’s preferences (not in anonymous form) and improve his personal use of services. These cookies are treated for 15 days. This type of cookies is only installed with the express consent of the user. To disable this type of cookies contact us at
support@oryxtechs.com
.
Third-parties Cookies:
these cookies are installed by third parties as a result of the mere use by the user of our services, and enable the same (i) access it via social networks (so-called “social plugin”), (ii) and to receive advertising customized.
More specifically, (i) the authentication through the “social plugin” allows the user to:
access and use the Services
share content on social networks.
The management of information collected by “third parties” shall be governed by the relevant information which you are referred. Below are the web addresses for the various information and to third-parties consent forms:
